Package: teachIRT
Type: Package
Title: Functions to Teach and Explore Item Response Theory
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Jan Killisch
Maintainer: Jan Killisch <jan.killisch@rptu.de>
Description: This is a very simple R-package that can be used to teach and 
  explore Item  Response Theory. The package is in not intended for actual 
  research or applied psychometrics in any way.
  The package provides functions to compute likelihood components and measures of
  observed information for unidimensional IRT models as well as some functions to
  plot them.
  Included models are
  - 1PL-3PL
  - (G)PCM
  - GRM
  The models are specified using a traditional IRT-parameterization.
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
